Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the air-to-ground channel in cellular-connected UAV communications, which involves networking and internet architecture aspects. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the optimization of uplink cell associations and power allocations over multiple resource blocks, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes centralized and decentralized ICIC schemes for optimal performance, which involves systems and control aspects. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the uplink transmission from a UAV to cellular BSs, which can involve multimedia aspects such as video or image transmission. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper proposes a centralized ICIC design based on the successive convex approximation (SCA) method, which involves computational engineering aspects.
